edu.iu.dsc.tws.api.tset.sets

Interface TSet<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the data set
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, TBase
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BatchTSet<T>, StreamingTSet<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BatchTSetImpl, CachedTSet, CheckpointedTSet, ComputeTSet, PersistedTSet, SComputeTSet, SourceTSet, SSinkTSet, SSourceTSet, StoredTSet, StreamingTSetImpl, WindowComputeTSet

    public interface TSet<T>
extends TBase
    Twister data set. A TSet would abstract a Task level computation (Source/ Compute or Sink) in a more user friendly API. A TSet would be followed by a TLink that would expose the communication level operations performed on the computation. Note the extensions of this interface BatchTSet and StreamingTSet. These would intimately separate out the operations based on the OperationMode of the data flow graph. This interface only specifies the common operations for Batch and Streaming operations.
